This paper deals with the problem of a robot manipulating an object on a tabletop, which is a common problem in robotics. The paper proposes a POMDP formulation to address the uncertainty in the object pose and incorporates constraints such as kinematic reachability, self-collision, and collision with obstacles. These are all topics that fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses a state-of-the-art online POMDP algorithm (DESPOT), which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with the control of a robot, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to solve the POMDP, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on simulated environments, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
